  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nBan `x / y` when x and y are integers, only allow `x // y`.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nIt's confusing coming from Python 3.x series and seeing `/` being used to divide integers. Vyper was designed when Python 2.7 was still in vogue, and at that time `/` meant floordiv. We should update Vyper syntax to match. `decimal` types would only be allowed to use `/`.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nTBD\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nAll source code that uses `/` will have to update.\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\nIf this VIP depends on any other VIPs being implemented, please mention them.\r\n\r\n## References\r\nAdd any references that this VIP might reference (other VIPs/issues, links to blog posts, etc.)\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
